    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="911"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1113</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ballantine</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="19" xml:id="d911fn19">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Minister in his despatch No. 851, March 9; received April 7.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-23">February 23,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 26</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 16 of January 23,
                        1931,<note n="20" xml:id="d911fn20">Not printed.</note> on the subject,
                    “Apparently Irregular Taxes Imposed on Foreign Goods at Wuchow”, and to the
                    Legation’s instruction of February 4, 1931,<note n="20" xml:id="d911fn22">Not
                        printed.</note> enclosing a copy of its note No. 244 to the Ministry of
                    Foreign Affairs,<note n="21" xml:id="d911fn21">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_985">p. 985</ref>.</note> I
                    have the honor to state that a communication has now been received from the
                    Mayor of Wuchow to the effect that instructions have been issued by the 8th
                    Route Army Headquarters at Wuchow directing that the assessment of the Hsiakwan
                    tax be discontinued. A copy of the note from the Mayor of Wuchow dated February
                    19, 1931, together with an English translation, is enclosed.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d911fn23">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Standard Oil Company has been informed of the contents of the communication
                    from the Mayor of Wuchow.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Ballantine</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
